The paper deals with decoding algorithms for convolutional codes, which are commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a low complexity decoder, which involves the use of shift registers and fast Fourier transform, indicating a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the decoder using complex numbers, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
